    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - INSTALL - REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Use a high quality grease on the individual needle bearings.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The reverse idler can be assembled in either the vertical or horizontal case position.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lubricate the idler shaft with oil before assembly. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the
                    CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the reverse idler inside diameter with grease. Insert the spacer in the reverse idler
                gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g0">Figure 160</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g0" filename="../figg13/g13026g0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 160. Insert Spacer in Reverse Idler Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the coated needle bearings on both sides of the reverse idler spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g1">Figure 161</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g1" filename="../figg13/g13026g1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 161. Install Coated Needle Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use grease on the reverse idler thrust washers to hold in place (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g2">Figure 162</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g2" filename="../figg13/g13026g2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 162. Use Grease on Reverse Idler Thrust Washers and Position Washer Tangs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position washer tangs to align the housing grooves (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g2">Figure 162</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the reverse idler assembly in the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g3">Figure 163</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g3" filename="../figg13/g13026g3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 163. Install Reverse Idler Assembly, Insert Idler Shaft, and Position Reverse Idler
                    Retainer
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the idler shaft into the case bore and line up the idler shaft lock groove with the
                lockscrew hole (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g3">Figure 163</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the reverse idler retainer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g3">Figure 163</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the lockscrew retaining bolt. Tighten the retainer to 20 to 25 ft-lbs. (27 to 34 N&#8226;
                m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g4">Figure 164</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g4" filename="../figg13/g13026g4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 164. Install Lockscrew Retaining Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
